  "narrative_arc": "Returns from prison to find his family evicted by the Dust Bowl and bank foreclosure. Joins the migration to California, where every promise of work is a trap. Steinbeck documents the economics of exploitation — how surplus labor drives wages below survival, how police serve growers, how government camps are the only humane response.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Tom Joad's dome maps climate displacement in the American context. Layer 9 (Environment — the Dust Bowl) destroys Layer 5 (Housing) and Layer 6 (Economic), creating mass migration that overwhelms every system in the destination. His story is climate migration before we had the term.",
